# [mandatory header]
# | Try to stay inside 50 Characters for header |
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

#  Allowed types:
#
#  build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#  ci: Changes to our CI configuration files and scripts
#  docs: Documentation only changes
#  feat: A new feature
#  fix: A bug fix
#  perf: A code change that improves performance
#  refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#  style: Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white-space,
#  formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
#  test: Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#  Append a `!` to indicate a breaking change

# [optional body]
# explain your changes, focusing on motivations

# [optional footer(s)]
# references to issues (e.g., "Closes #95")

# [optional] BREAKING CHANGE: introduce breaking change

# Specification: https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/#specification
